latestPosts.caption:
Introducing @deepikapadukone for Marie Claire’s 2025 Motherhood Issue 💛

Since bursting onto the scene nearly two decades ago, Padukone has always presented as the picture-perfect heroine—a megawatt Movie Star with nearly 40 film credits to her name, who regularly tops “highest paid actress” lists in India and is one-half of Bollywood’s It Couple (her husband is fellow actor Ranveer Singh). 

But there’s a new role she’s settling into: Deepika the Mom. 

Since the birth of her daughter last fall, Padukone is surrendering to the unknown, the uneasy. At the link in bio, the actress opens up about how having a daughter has re-centered her universe.

A question I get asked ever so often…
Bengaluru or Mumbai?

Ten years ago in March, our founder, Deepika Padukone, broke the silence on mental illness —sharing her experience with depression on national television. 

In a heartfelt conversation with NDTV, alongside her mother, Ujjala Padukone, our chairperson, Dr. Shyam Bhat, and our trustee, Anna Chandy, she opened up about her journey—encouraging others to speak up about their own mental health. 

This moment sparked a crucial conversation across the country and marked the beginning of The Live Love Laugh Foundation’s journey to champion mental health awareness and support.

#MentalHealthForAll #LiveLoveLaugh #MentalHealthMatters
